response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Sum of Squares\", \"description\": \"Find the sum of the squares of all numbers from 1 to n. Write a function `sum_of_squares` that takes an integer `n` as input and returns the sum of the squares of all numbers from 1 to `n`. For example, if you call `sum_of_squares(3)`, it should return `14`, which is `1^2 + 2^2 + 3^2`.\", \"code\": \"\\ndef sum_of_squares(n: int) -> int:\\n    total = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n+1):\\n        total += i ** 2\\n    return total\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_of_squares(3) == 14\", \"assert sum_of_squares(10) == 385\", \"assert sum_of_squares(5) == 55\"] }"
